        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Add Japanese (ja) localization",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Adds a complete Japanese (`ja`) localization: `ja.lproj/Localizable.strings` with all 1033 keys translated, following Apple's macOS Japanese UI conventions (キーチェーン for Keychain, メニューバー for menu bar, です・ます style for descriptions, concise noun phrases for buttons/labels).\n- Adds `AppLanguage.japanese` so 日本語 appears in the Settings → General language picker.\n- Adds the `language_japanese` label key to every existing language catalog (native-language renderings: Japonés, Японська, 日语, …).\n- Extends `LocalizationLanguageCatalogTests` so the catalog completeness check covers the new key.\n\n## Testing\n\n- `swift test --filter Localization` — all 21 tests across 6 localization suites pass.\n- Full `swift test` (3427 tests): the only failure is `MiniMaxMenuCardModelTests` \"minimax token plan model shows weekly quota and points balance\", which also fails on `main` on any machine whose system locale is Japanese — `subscriptionDateString` (MenuCardView.swift) formats with `Locale.current`, so the expected English date renders as 2027年5月18日. Pre-existing and unrelated to this change; happy to fix it in a follow-up if useful.\n- Verified `ja.lproj` is included in the built `CodexBar_CodexBar.bundle` and the app runs with Japanese UI when the language is selected.\n\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)",
